WEBVTT

00:07.208 --> 00:09.609
You look good, olivia.

00:09.610 --> 00:12.011
Looks can be deceiving, though,
can't they?

00:12.013 --> 00:14.413
I see you have
a few more locks.

00:14.415 --> 00:16.449
That's good.

00:16.450 --> 00:18.484
You can never be too careful,
can you?

00:18.486 --> 00:20.085
What do you want?

00:20.087 --> 00:22.054
I have a problem --

00:22.056 --> 00:23.889
A rather big one,
actually,

00:23.890 --> 00:25.723
And since you're a fixer,
i thought i'd come to you.

00:25.726 --> 00:29.028
You see, apparently
there's a group of people

00:29.030 --> 00:31.463
Who have decided
that i'm a criminal.

00:31.465 --> 00:35.534
They're building a case,
some preposterous claim

00:35.536 --> 00:39.505
About a top-secret
spy organization called b613

00:39.507 --> 00:42.408
That i'm<i> supposedly</i>
the head of.

00:42.410 --> 00:46.578
I mean, have you ever heard
anything so ridiculous?

00:46.580 --> 00:48.814
Anyway, i'd be happy
to shut it down myself,

00:48.816 --> 00:51.250
But i'm just a paleontologist
at the smithsonian

00:51.252 --> 00:53.318
And i don't think my methods
would work,

00:53.320 --> 00:57.756
So i'm giving you a chance --

00:57.758 --> 00:59.658
One chance --

00:59.660 --> 01:01.393
To shut it down
yourself.

01:01.395 --> 01:04.096
If you can do that
in the next 48 hours...

01:04.098 --> 01:05.831
I'm not lifting a finger
for you.

01:05.833 --> 01:08.467
Tell me, who do you think
stands to lose the most

01:08.469 --> 01:10.769
When this so-called b613
is made public --

01:10.771 --> 01:13.072
The quiet paleontologist
collecting bones

01:13.074 --> 01:14.473
Or the man down the street

01:14.475 --> 01:16.341
Who could have pulled the plug
on it and didn't?

01:16.343 --> 01:19.578
Who, in fact,
actively participated,

01:19.580 --> 01:21.213
Put his own man
at the helm,

01:21.215 --> 01:23.282
Using him
to service his own agenda --

01:23.284 --> 01:25.417
I don't care
about any of that.

01:25.419 --> 01:27.186
I care about justice.

01:27.188 --> 01:29.788
You say that to me now
because you're angry at me,

01:29.790 --> 01:33.125
But think
who we are talking about,

01:33.127 --> 01:36.862
What you have done for him,
the things you've sacrificed.

01:36.864 --> 01:39.298
Is your hatred for me
so great --

01:41.368 --> 01:44.103
[ laughs ]

01:44.105 --> 01:49.441
So great that you are willing
to tear him down, too?

01:49.443 --> 01:50.843
Ah.

01:50.845 --> 01:53.445
[ laughs ]

01:53.447 --> 01:54.446
I see.

01:54.448 --> 01:56.515
Something's changed.

01:56.517 --> 01:59.451
Did he disappoint you?

01:59.453 --> 02:03.856
Not live up to your
very, very high standards?

02:03.858 --> 02:07.259
Fail to meet
your expectation of perfection?

02:07.261 --> 02:11.263
Did you learn
that he's only human after all?

02:11.265 --> 02:12.664
[ laughing ] oh.

02:12.666 --> 02:15.801
You want to dig
into some freud, baby?

02:15.803 --> 02:18.103
[ laughs ]

02:18.104 --> 02:20.404
Are you finding that no matter
how far you run,

02:20.407 --> 02:23.208
No matter
how white the knight...

02:23.210 --> 02:24.643
[ laughs ]

02:24.645 --> 02:29.314
That all men, in fact,
are just like your father?

02:29.316 --> 02:32.217
Don't talk about me
like you know me.

02:32.219 --> 02:33.652
You don't know me.

02:33.654 --> 02:39.191
It is your friends
who do not know you,

02:39.193 --> 02:41.793
But i do.

02:41.795 --> 02:45.898
You are a warrior --

02:45.900 --> 02:48.834
Never reckless,
never naive,

02:48.836 --> 02:51.904
Too smart
to let fear drive you.

02:51.906 --> 02:55.807
Precise, quiet, calculating,

02:55.809 --> 02:58.377
You will wait
for the right time.

02:58.379 --> 03:01.213
You will look
at all the possible outcomes.

03:01.215 --> 03:03.849
You'll understand
what needs to be done.

03:03.851 --> 03:05.250
You will pick a side

03:05.252 --> 03:07.319
And then you will handle
this situation

03:07.321 --> 03:09.922
In the manner we both know
it needs to be handled.

03:09.924 --> 03:13.692
You will burn it down
and never look back.

03:13.694 --> 03:15.527
Your friends don't know you.

03:15.529 --> 03:17.896
They think
you're loyal to people.

03:17.898 --> 03:19.498
They don't know that you

03:19.500 --> 03:22.801
Would use them as kindling
for the fire if have to.

03:22.803 --> 03:24.703
<i>I</i> know you.

03:24.705 --> 03:28.240
I know that you would never
allow people to get in the way

03:28.242 --> 03:30.709
Of what is right,
of your fundamental belief

03:30.711 --> 03:34.479
That the republic must stand
at all costs.

03:34.481 --> 03:37.900
I know you,

03:37.901 --> 03:41.320
Because the apple does not fall
far from the tree, olivia,

03:41.322 --> 03:43.922
Poison though it may be.

03:43.924 --> 03:46.792
It's time
for you to leave.

03:50.231 --> 03:52.564
Thank you for the wine,
olivia.

03:54.435 --> 03:57.302
Mmm.
Excellent, as always.

03:58.606 --> 04:01.573
[ russell groans ]

04:01.575 --> 04:02.975
Oh.

04:02.977 --> 04:04.676
Russell, is it?

04:04.678 --> 04:08.981
I'm sorry for the inconvenience,
russell.

04:08.983 --> 04:11.016
It's a very light sedative,
really.

04:11.018 --> 04:14.686
He'll wake up with a painful
hangover and a bit of amnesia.

04:14.688 --> 04:16.655
You didn't have to bring him
into this at all.
I did.

04:16.657 --> 04:18.590
The alternative was
to kill him.

04:18.592 --> 04:21.260
Would you have preferred
i go that route?

04:21.262 --> 04:22.327
This is how to reach me.

04:22.329 --> 04:24.830
48 hours.

04:24.831 --> 04:27.332
I'm giving you 48 hours
to realize that i am right

04:27.334 --> 04:29.635
And to figure out a way
to end this nonsense.

04:44.551 --> 04:46.885
[ giggles ]

04:47.488 --> 04:49.354
Hey.

04:49.356 --> 04:50.756
What happened?

04:50.758 --> 04:53.892
I think we had a little bit
too much to drink.

04:53.894 --> 04:55.027
[ giggles ]

04:55.029 --> 04:56.595
We did?

04:56.597 --> 04:58.297
I --

04:58.299 --> 05:00.666
You don't remember?
[ giggles ]

05:00.668 --> 05:03.568
Three bottles of wine.

05:03.570 --> 05:07.673
Okay, but you do remember
the dancing?

05:07.675 --> 05:10.042
The singing?

05:10.044 --> 05:13.312
Oh, tell me you remember
the singing,

05:13.314 --> 05:16.682
Because it was amazing.

05:16.684 --> 05:18.417
I sang?

05:18.419 --> 05:19.785
[ both laugh ]

05:19.787 --> 05:23.855
Come on,
let's get you into bed.

05:23.857 --> 05:26.325
[ chuckles ]

05:27.394 --> 05:28.660
Oh, go get in bed.

05:28.662 --> 05:31.730
I'll be right there.

05:31.732 --> 05:33.765
[ giggles ]

05:38.806 --> 05:51.016
[ breathing heavily ]

05:51.018 --> 05:52.551
48 hours
to shut down the case.

05:52.553 --> 05:54.036
And if we don't?

05:54.037 --> 05:55.520
My father will take matters
into his own hands.

05:55.522 --> 05:57.089
Which is why
we need to fast-track --

05:57.091 --> 05:59.791
Convene a grand jury,
start seeking indictments.

05:59.793 --> 06:00.892
Do we have the evidence?

06:00.894 --> 06:02.327
With jake's testimony,
yes.

06:02.328 --> 06:03.761
I served under rowan,
killed at his behest,

06:03.764 --> 06:05.664
Inherited missions from him
when i became command.

06:05.666 --> 06:07.132
If anyone can nail this guy,
it's me.

06:07.134 --> 06:08.751
Your father's right,
though.

06:08.752 --> 06:10.369
Taking this case public
exposes the president

06:10.371 --> 06:11.403
To a great deal of risk.

06:11.405 --> 06:12.604
Is everyone okay with that?

06:14.441 --> 06:16.441
Liv?

06:17.644 --> 06:20.078
If that's the cost of
taking down my father, yes.

06:20.080 --> 06:22.581
All right, then.
We are going after rowan.

06:22.583 --> 06:24.649
Let's talk strategy.

06:24.651 --> 06:26.418
[<i> camera shutter clicks</i> ]

06:26.420 --> 06:27.986
I know you hate the bill.

06:27.987 --> 06:29.553
What you have to ask yourself
is whether you're willing

06:29.556 --> 06:31.123
To give up the senate
for it.

06:31.125 --> 06:32.924
Because come mid-terms,
i'll make sure

06:32.926 --> 06:35.093
You don't have a dime
in your campaign coffers.

06:35.095 --> 06:38.463
I'm pleased to hear that,
senator.

06:38.465 --> 06:40.665
Jenson's in. There's only three
holdouts, people.

06:40.667 --> 06:42.768
Man: Yeah!
[ applause ]

06:42.770 --> 06:45.404
...Watching the senate floor
where they're gathering to vote

06:45.406 --> 06:46.838
On sweeping
and historic legislation.

06:46.840 --> 06:49.408
The so-called "brandon bill"
rose from the ashes

06:49.410 --> 06:51.143
Of brandon parker's
fatal shooting

06:51.145 --> 06:53.545
By former police officer
jeffrey newton.

06:53.547 --> 06:55.447
Who's left
of the holdouts?

06:55.449 --> 06:56.581
Hobart, wexler, peters.

06:56.583 --> 06:57.582
Wexler's not budging.

06:57.584 --> 06:58.850
Leak that wexler caved.

06:58.852 --> 07:00.352
But wexler<i> didn't</i> cave.

07:00.354 --> 07:01.520
Mr. Beene just said --

07:01.522 --> 07:02.521
Leak that he's in.

07:02.523 --> 07:03.922
Hobart and peters
hate wexler.

07:03.924 --> 07:05.741
They'll never check
with him,

07:05.742 --> 07:07.559
And neither of those two
want to be the last holdout.

07:08.195 --> 07:10.095
Do it.
Make the call.

07:10.097 --> 07:11.663
Bnc can now safely report

07:11.665 --> 07:14.666
That the brandon bill
will pass the senate today.

07:14.668 --> 07:16.318
Yes!
Yes!

07:16.319 --> 07:17.969
[ applause ]
well done, everyone.

07:17.971 --> 07:20.839
[ light laughter ]

07:20.841 --> 07:23.142
Uh!

07:23.143 --> 07:25.444
Prep a big bill signing event
for this afternoon.

07:25.446 --> 07:27.329
Huge!

07:27.330 --> 07:29.213
Rose garden, tons of cops --
in uniform behind the president.

07:29.216 --> 07:30.849
And the victims' families.

07:30.851 --> 07:32.184
I want brandon's father there.

07:32.186 --> 07:36.521
It's a great day
for the country, cy.

07:36.523 --> 07:38.623
Not so bad for us,
either.

07:38.625 --> 07:40.959
Now we get
the black vote.

07:40.961 --> 07:45.464
Imagine it if you can --
black people voting republican!

07:45.466 --> 07:47.466
Naming their kids
after fitzgerald grant,

07:47.468 --> 07:49.768
Putting his picture
on the dining room wall.

07:49.770 --> 07:51.069
The democrats won't know
what hit them.

07:51.071 --> 07:52.070
That's gross.

07:52.072 --> 07:53.672
I know, red.

07:53.674 --> 07:54.806
I know.

07:54.808 --> 07:56.675
We'll have more
once voting begins

07:56.677 --> 07:59.144
For what's shaping up
to be a truly historic day

07:59.146 --> 08:01.396
For the grant administration.

08:01.397 --> 08:03.647
But until then, let's return you
to your local affiliates.

08:03.650 --> 08:06.518
Well, folks, she baked her way
into the national spotlight.

08:06.520 --> 08:08.987
We'll meet the local baker
who's taking top prize

08:08.989 --> 08:11.523
At the national cupcake show
in just a moment.

08:11.525 --> 08:13.625
But first, let's go live
to patricia waters,

08:13.627 --> 08:15.627
Who's covering
the d.C. Mayoral race.

08:15.629 --> 08:17.162
Patricia,
what can you tell us?

08:17.164 --> 08:18.797
Things seem to be
really heating up

08:18.799 --> 08:20.499
Between incumbent
d.C. Mayor verrano

08:20.501 --> 08:22.968
And his challenger,
local activist marcus walker.

08:22.970 --> 08:25.770
Walker is now leading the
three-term mayor by nine points.

08:25.772 --> 08:27.689
I think it's safe to say

08:27.690 --> 08:29.607
That marcus walker is feeling
pretty good right now.

08:29.610 --> 08:31.576
[ doorbell rings ]

08:31.578 --> 08:33.545
[ knocking on door ]

08:33.547 --> 08:35.313
Marcus?

08:39.119 --> 08:40.702
I don't get it.

08:40.703 --> 08:42.286
Have you even spoken to marcus
since brandon parker?

08:42.289 --> 08:44.623
And why did he call us
to the mayor's house?

08:45.692 --> 08:48.593
Huck: No one's here, the door's
unlocked -- not good.

08:48.595 --> 08:50.595
Marcus?

08:50.597 --> 08:52.664
Marcus: Up here.

08:58.238 --> 09:01.306
I tried to stop the bleeding,
but there was --

09:01.308 --> 09:03.241
There was so much blood.

09:03.243 --> 09:04.576
I'm gonna need you
to stay right there.

09:04.578 --> 09:05.610
Wait a minute.
Is that who i think it is?

09:05.612 --> 09:07.946
The mayor's wife? Yes.

09:12.553 --> 09:15.720
All right, marcus.
Tell us what happened.

09:15.722 --> 09:17.372
We were here in the bed,

09:17.373 --> 09:19.023
And we heard someone
come in the back door.

09:19.026 --> 09:20.592
Figured
it was her husband.

09:22.296 --> 09:23.662
You said he went in early.
He did.

09:23.664 --> 09:25.330
Now he's home.
Go in there.

09:27.100 --> 09:28.667
Marcus, please.

09:30.070 --> 09:32.203
Marcus: So i hid.

09:32.205 --> 09:33.572
Over there.

09:33.574 --> 09:35.040
I could see through the door,

09:35.042 --> 09:36.308
Through the reflection
in the mirror.

09:36.310 --> 09:37.309
I could see everything.

09:37.311 --> 09:38.710
What did you see?

09:38.712 --> 09:40.879
H-hey, baby.
Did you forget something?

09:40.881 --> 09:42.948
I wasn't -- ahhh!

09:42.950 --> 09:44.349
[ screams ]

09:44.351 --> 09:45.684
Ahh!

09:45.686 --> 09:46.952
Oh, my god!
[ screams ]

09:46.954 --> 09:49.187
She barely had a chance
to scream --

09:49.189 --> 09:50.622
It all happened so fast.

09:50.624 --> 09:51.790
Next thing i know,

09:51.792 --> 09:54.225
Two more dudes in masks
come rushing in.

09:54.227 --> 09:55.627
Man: Damn.
You snapped her neck.

09:55.629 --> 09:57.195
You were supposed to make it
look like...

09:57.197 --> 09:58.697
What the hell?
She bit my hand.

09:58.699 --> 09:59.831
Stab her anyway.

09:59.833 --> 10:01.700
Got on my last nerve.

10:04.371 --> 10:05.670
You happy now?

10:07.874 --> 10:09.107
I count five stab wounds --

10:09.109 --> 10:11.076
Used something
with a clip point like a...

10:11.078 --> 10:12.377
Hunting knife?

10:12.846 --> 10:14.746
What happened next?

10:17.818 --> 10:19.384
Get the diamonds.

10:19.386 --> 10:21.219
Hey, don't forget
to grab the necklace.

10:21.221 --> 10:23.688
Man: Okay!
Okay, let's go!

10:25.359 --> 10:28.893
I count three different sets
of shoe prints on the carpet.

10:28.895 --> 10:30.729
Also marcus doesn't have
a scratch on him.

10:30.731 --> 10:32.731
The mayor's wife
would have fought back.

10:32.733 --> 10:33.999
So he's telling the truth.

10:34.000 --> 10:35.266
So option "a" --
we call the police,

10:35.268 --> 10:36.768
Represent him till his
defense attorney arrives,

10:36.770 --> 10:38.403
Ask the cops to be discreet?

10:38.404 --> 10:40.037
No, we can't ask the cops
for anything right now.

10:40.040 --> 10:41.906
Marcus isn't exactly popular
with the dcpd.

10:41.908 --> 10:43.408
They're not gonna help.

10:43.409 --> 10:44.909
So then it's option "b."
can we do option "b"?

10:44.911 --> 10:46.144
Huck:
We can do option "b."

10:46.146 --> 10:48.113
Marcus: What's option "b"?

10:48.114 --> 10:50.081
Goodbye, homicidal burglary.
Hello, missing person.

10:50.083 --> 10:52.350
Ah, this never happened,
you were never here.

10:52.352 --> 10:54.886
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

10:54.888 --> 10:56.688
Cy.

10:56.690 --> 10:58.723
We have a problem
with the brandon bill.

10:58.725 --> 10:59.958
It's senator rogers, sir.

10:59.960 --> 11:01.092
Her office called --

11:01.094 --> 11:02.827
She went into labor
this morning.

11:02.829 --> 11:04.362
A week early?
A week early.

11:04.364 --> 11:06.431
We moved up the vote.
A week early.

11:06.433 --> 11:08.100
[ sighs ]

11:08.101 --> 11:09.768
Without rogers,
do we still win this?

11:09.770 --> 11:11.836
Without rogers, it's a tie --
49 to 49,

11:11.838 --> 11:14.205
Courtesy of virginia's
empty senate seat.

11:14.207 --> 11:15.707
Should i reach out
to the vice president, sir?

11:15.709 --> 11:17.308
Get her out there
on the floor, cy.

11:17.310 --> 11:18.443
We need this bill to pass.

11:18.445 --> 11:19.878
That's what
she's there for.

11:22.783 --> 11:24.749
...T-i-o-n. Asphyxiation.

11:24.751 --> 11:26.151
That is correct.

11:26.153 --> 11:27.986
[ applause ]

11:27.988 --> 11:29.788
Which means if the next word
is spelled correctly,

11:29.790 --> 11:32.023
Violet lee will be
our champion speller.

11:32.025 --> 11:36.094
So, here to read that next word
is our very special guest judge,

11:36.096 --> 11:37.829
Vice president susan ross.

11:37.831 --> 11:41.466
[ applause ]
hello, children.

11:41.468 --> 11:43.134
The next word will be --

11:43.136 --> 11:44.736
I need a moment, ma'am.

11:44.738 --> 11:46.971
[ whispering ]

11:46.973 --> 11:49.040
I'm not leaving
until the bee is over,

11:49.042 --> 11:51.042
Until the last word
has been spelled.

11:51.044 --> 11:52.177
[ whispering ]

11:52.179 --> 11:54.412
I'm sorry, honey.
Here we go.

11:54.414 --> 11:57.048
The next word will be
"onomatopoeia."

11:57.050 --> 12:00.085
Onomatopoeia.

12:00.087 --> 12:03.088
O-n-o...

12:03.090 --> 12:07.125
M-a-t...

12:07.127 --> 12:11.396
O-p...O...

12:11.398 --> 12:15.300
E...I...

12:15.302 --> 12:16.434
A?

12:16.436 --> 12:18.737
Ono--
that is correct, violet!

12:18.739 --> 12:19.971
You win!

12:19.973 --> 12:22.373
[ applause ]
congratulations.

12:22.375 --> 12:25.877
And please, everybody,
keep reading.

12:26.413 --> 12:28.246
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]
cy: We have a tie in the senate.

12:28.248 --> 12:29.414
Today's your big day!

12:29.416 --> 12:31.082
To vote
on the brandon bill.

12:31.084 --> 12:32.284
[ sighs ]

12:32.285 --> 12:33.485
To vote "yes"
on the brandon bill.

12:33.487 --> 12:36.054
But i haven't read it,
not since it was first proposed,

12:36.056 --> 12:37.456
Not the final draft.

12:37.457 --> 12:38.857
It is very much like
the previous drafts.

12:38.859 --> 12:40.425
Well, i'll have to read it
first.

12:40.427 --> 12:41.960
Susan.
[ chuckles ]

12:41.962 --> 12:44.028
The bill is
1,200 pages long.

12:44.030 --> 12:45.997
Then i better
get cracking.

12:45.999 --> 12:47.031
Ho, no, no.

12:47.033 --> 12:49.100
They've already
begun voting.

12:49.102 --> 12:51.336
Then they're gonna
have to wait.

12:51.338 --> 12:53.471
I won't vote on something
i haven't read, cyrus.

12:53.473 --> 12:56.307
And i don't think the american
people would want me to.

12:58.311 --> 13:00.445
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

13:00.447 --> 13:02.280
What should we do
with the body?

13:02.282 --> 13:03.414
Dealer's choice.

13:03.416 --> 13:04.849
Really? Thanks, huck.

13:04.851 --> 13:06.184
No problem.

13:06.185 --> 13:07.518
I think we go old school
on this one --

13:07.521 --> 13:08.820
Classic fluff and fold?

13:08.822 --> 13:10.355
Less blood, easy roll out.
Works for me.

13:10.357 --> 13:14.559
¶ i'm your boogie man,
that's what i am ¶

13:14.561 --> 13:18.530
¶ i'm here to do
whatever i can ¶

13:18.532 --> 13:22.834
