24:51.991 --> 24:53.257
I see.

24:53.259 --> 24:55.259
With how many people aboard?

24:55.261 --> 24:58.128
329.

24:59.565 --> 25:01.966
And the pilot that obeyed
that order

25:01.968 --> 25:04.034
To shoot down the plane --
who was that?

25:04.036 --> 25:05.102
Do you have name?

25:06.739 --> 25:08.194
Why?

25:08.195 --> 25:09.650
Because he could testify
against rowan.

25:09.651 --> 25:11.106
I need the name, jake.
This is big.

25:17.750 --> 25:19.650
His name
was fitzgerald grant.

25:25.992 --> 25:27.758
The president?

25:27.760 --> 25:29.193
Yes.

25:48.080 --> 25:50.714
[ elevator bell dings ]

26:22.982 --> 26:25.749
It's me.

26:28.020 --> 26:29.820
[ sighs ]

26:29.822 --> 26:31.088
Come in.

26:31.090 --> 26:33.157
Hey.

26:33.159 --> 26:36.077
Are you coming in?

26:36.078 --> 26:38.996
I'm not a heavy drinker,
and i never sing or lose time.

26:38.998 --> 26:40.331
And there's a whole piece
of our last evening together

26:40.333 --> 26:42.232
That's just gone.

26:45.871 --> 26:47.338
Will you please
just come in?

26:47.340 --> 26:49.306
I came over because you called
and sounded upset,

26:49.308 --> 26:51.241
And i wanted to make sure
you were okay.

26:52.745 --> 26:54.378
[ sighs ]

26:54.379 --> 26:56.012
And you are beautiful
and very sexy --

26:56.015 --> 26:59.717
Incredibly...Sexy.

26:59.719 --> 27:01.118
And a lot of fun --
believe me,

27:01.120 --> 27:03.253
I've enjoyed every minute
of our time together,

27:03.255 --> 27:08.125
But this whole alex thing is,
uh...

27:08.127 --> 27:12.096
I'm looking for something
more stable.

27:12.098 --> 27:13.831
So...

27:23.943 --> 27:29.313
My life is
very...Complicated.

27:29.315 --> 27:33.851
And i want it
to<i> not</i> be complicated.

27:33.853 --> 27:38.822
And i'm with you,
when i'm alex,

27:38.824 --> 27:41.992
Nothing is complicated.

27:44.130 --> 27:45.295
I want that.

27:47.299 --> 27:50.267
I need that.

27:54.140 --> 27:57.141
Will you please come in?

27:57.143 --> 27:58.175
Olivia --

27:58.177 --> 28:00.277
Not olivia.

28:01.614 --> 28:04.415
[ chuckles softly ]

28:04.417 --> 28:07.451
Alex.

28:07.453 --> 28:09.920
Alex.

28:33.412 --> 28:36.313
[ moans ]

28:50.229 --> 28:52.463
[ moans ]

28:58.003 --> 29:00.437
[ laughs ]

29:13.986 --> 29:15.085
[ knock on door ]

29:15.087 --> 29:17.121
How's it going in here?

29:17.123 --> 29:19.040
Mrs. Grant!
You're a lawyer.

29:19.041 --> 29:20.958
In fact, didn't you do better
in law school than your husband?

29:20.960 --> 29:22.059
Weren't you first
in your class?

29:22.061 --> 29:23.193
I read that somewhere.
[ chuckles ]

29:23.195 --> 29:24.528
Come in. Sit down.

29:24.530 --> 29:25.829
Maybe you can answer
my questions.

29:25.831 --> 29:28.349
[ laughs ]

29:28.350 --> 29:30.868
I'd be happy to -- and i'm sure
your questions are spot-on --

29:30.870 --> 29:34.271
But, susan,
we are running out of time.

29:34.273 --> 29:37.174
The country needs
this bill now.

29:37.176 --> 29:39.443
The president needs
this bill now.

29:39.445 --> 29:41.378
And<i> you</i> need
this bill now.

29:43.349 --> 29:44.348
So you can announce
your senate run.

29:45.351 --> 29:46.817
Who told you that?

29:46.819 --> 29:49.052
No one.
I just assumed.

29:49.054 --> 29:50.320
I mean, let's be honest,

29:50.322 --> 29:52.256
That's the real reason
i'm here, right?

29:52.258 --> 29:54.792
So you can take my senate seat
and then not have to worry

29:54.794 --> 29:56.927
About a competitive v.P.
When you run for president.

29:56.929 --> 29:58.195
[ chuckles ]

29:58.197 --> 30:00.898
It's a genius plan.

30:00.900 --> 30:03.333
You'd make an excellent
president, mrs. Grant.

30:03.335 --> 30:04.401
[ exhales sharply ]

30:04.403 --> 30:06.303
So, what do you think
of the bill?

30:06.305 --> 30:09.339
Because for the life of me,
i cannot wrap my head around

30:09.341 --> 30:10.507
The section
on federal oversight.

30:10.509 --> 30:11.508
Can you?

30:11.510 --> 30:14.378
I...

30:14.380 --> 30:17.181
Have to confess that i have not
read it...

30:17.183 --> 30:18.315
In its entirety.

30:18.317 --> 30:19.383
Oh.

30:19.385 --> 30:20.517
[ sighs ]

30:20.519 --> 30:22.986
Well, you should.

30:22.988 --> 30:24.972
Mm.

30:24.973 --> 30:26.957
'cause you'll get questions.
Once you announce.

30:26.959 --> 30:29.459
So, do you think that i will be
able to announce soon?

30:29.461 --> 30:30.561
Hard to say.

30:30.563 --> 30:32.029
Oh.

30:32.031 --> 30:34.031
I mean, at this point,
i could be here all night.

30:34.033 --> 30:36.300
I was gonna order dinner.
You hungry?

30:36.302 --> 30:38.302
Mnh.

30:38.304 --> 30:41.238
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

30:41.240 --> 30:43.340
Quinn: The mayor kills his wife
and can't be touched.

30:43.342 --> 30:44.908
He's got the whole city
in his pocket --

30:44.910 --> 30:46.460
Cops, unions, judges.

30:46.461 --> 30:48.011
No sign of anyone named mickey.
[ television playing
in background ]

30:48.013 --> 30:49.379
There's always another move.

30:49.381 --> 30:51.415
[ sighs ] i think my next move's
to throw up.

30:51.417 --> 30:52.449
Stop.
I'm not really gonna --

30:52.451 --> 30:54.852
No, the tv. Pause it.

30:54.854 --> 30:55.853
Go back.

30:55.855 --> 30:57.020
What is it?

30:57.022 --> 30:59.423
Natalie fought the guys,
right?

30:59.425 --> 31:01.091
See the bandage?

31:01.093 --> 31:02.743
Oh, my god.

31:02.744 --> 31:04.394
We've been looking for mickey.
Mickey isn't his name.

31:04.396 --> 31:05.896
Wait -- why do you say that?

31:05.898 --> 31:07.097
Oh. Ohh.

31:07.099 --> 31:08.265
What?

31:08.267 --> 31:10.100
Wait, why isn't that his --
oh.

31:10.102 --> 31:11.635
Wow. I see. The ears.

31:11.637 --> 31:12.870
The ears.
The ears.

31:12.872 --> 31:14.137
So big.
So very big.

31:14.139 --> 31:15.939
Mickey's a nickname.

31:15.941 --> 31:17.407
That's our guy.

31:17.409 --> 31:19.042
Quinn:
Marvin helmsley o'connor.

31:19.044 --> 31:20.477
"mickey" to his friends.

31:20.479 --> 31:21.545
Huck: Been mayor verrano's
personal driver

31:21.547 --> 31:23.430
For the past 13 years.

31:23.431 --> 31:25.314
Also a longtime associate
of the burnham crime family.

31:25.317 --> 31:27.251
Something the mayor doesn't
exactly like to advertise.

31:27.253 --> 31:29.319
I hacked into the gps
of mickey's town car --

31:29.321 --> 31:31.154
He was parked outside
the mayor's house

31:31.156 --> 31:32.222
At the time of the murder.

31:32.224 --> 31:33.590
Quinn:
Also hacked his cellphone --

31:33.592 --> 31:35.893
One call right before the
murder, one call right after.

31:35.895 --> 31:37.678
And a $20,000 deposit

31:37.679 --> 31:39.462
Appeared in his offshore account
the next day.

31:39.465 --> 31:42.399
He breaks in, fakes a robbery,
kills his boss's cheating wife,

31:42.401 --> 31:43.433
And collects 20 grand.

31:43.435 --> 31:44.918
Hell of a tip.

31:44.919 --> 31:46.402
So, that's it?
We can nail this guy?

31:46.405 --> 31:47.971
Put verrano away?

31:49.408 --> 31:50.574
With that evidence?
No.

31:50.576 --> 31:52.976
To put verrano away
would require

31:52.978 --> 31:55.045
Either forensic evidence...
Which we cleaned up.

31:55.047 --> 31:57.114
...Or witness testimony.

31:57.116 --> 31:58.832
That's you, marcus.

31:58.833 --> 32:00.549
You have to testify
if what you want is justice

32:00.552 --> 32:02.219
For natalie verrano's death.

32:02.221 --> 32:04.688
If you don't, i can work out
a deal with the mayor,

32:04.690 --> 32:06.056
Leverage the threat
of your testimony

32:06.058 --> 32:07.157
To get him to drop out
of the race.

32:07.159 --> 32:09.159
You'll win.
Let me get this straight.

32:09.161 --> 32:11.461
I hire you, and you tell me
to go on record

32:11.463 --> 32:13.497
Saying i was sleeping
with verrano's wife.

32:13.499 --> 32:16.466
I didn't know you got paid
to ruin people's careers.

32:16.468 --> 32:19.503
Justice or your career.

32:19.505 --> 32:22.339
I can only get you one.

32:22.341 --> 32:24.641
So, what do you want?

32:29.014 --> 32:30.380
You're going to go first.

32:30.381 --> 32:31.747
You're going to announce that
you will finish out your term,

32:31.748 --> 32:33.114
But that you are pulling out
of the race.

32:33.115 --> 32:34.481
You're going to endorse
marcus walker for mayor.

32:34.486 --> 32:36.320
And then you will say
that you're going to ake it

32:36.322 --> 32:38.088
Your personal crusade
to find your missing wife,

32:38.090 --> 32:39.589
And then you will disappear
from public life.

32:39.591 --> 32:41.692
You will express your sympathies
to mayor verrano.

32:41.694 --> 32:43.260
You will tell him how sorry
you are

32:43.262 --> 32:45.162
That he leaves the campaign
under these circumstances,

32:45.164 --> 32:46.697
And then you will humbly
accept his endorsement.

32:46.699 --> 32:48.031
And that's it.

32:48.033 --> 32:50.667
You will both keep it
short and simple.

32:50.669 --> 32:52.202
You will answer no questions.

32:52.204 --> 32:54.204
We will return to this car
and drive away.

32:54.206 --> 32:55.539
Do you have any questions?

32:57.476 --> 33:00.544
That bitch got
what was coming to her.

33:00.546 --> 33:03.480
Remember that.

33:07.453 --> 33:12.255
As i've said, this is
the hardest day of my life.

33:12.257 --> 33:15.525
But i'm comforted knowing
that the city that i love

33:15.527 --> 33:18.495
Is gonna be in good hands
with marcus walker.

33:18.497 --> 33:20.497
Thank you for your support.

33:22.267 --> 33:25.635
[ applause ]

33:25.637 --> 33:27.604
Thank you, mayor verrano.

33:31.510 --> 33:33.744
My whole life has been
about justice.

33:33.746 --> 33:36.013
Fighting for what's right.

33:36.015 --> 33:40.117
Dr. King said
a lie cannot live forever.

33:40.119 --> 33:42.519
I've tried
to expose those lies.

33:42.521 --> 33:44.354
I've tried to live the truth.

33:44.356 --> 33:46.790
I want to do that as your mayor,
but i can't.

33:46.792 --> 33:49.359
Because this is a lie.

33:49.361 --> 33:51.428
The mayor's wife is not missing.
She's dead.

33:51.430 --> 33:53.480
[ indistinct shouting ]
he killed her.

33:53.481 --> 33:55.531
Just a minute!
He killed her because i was
having an affair with her.

33:55.534 --> 33:57.534
[ crowd shouting indistinctly ]
i'm sorry.

33:57.536 --> 33:59.569
I am a sinner.

33:59.571 --> 34:02.005
But he is a murderer.
That is the truth.

34:02.007 --> 34:03.707
And this...
Man: Mr. Mayor!

34:03.709 --> 34:06.076
This is a lie.

34:06.078 --> 34:07.310
[ indistinct shouting ]

34:11.350 --> 34:13.617
It's been 24 hours
and we still don't know

34:13.619 --> 34:14.935
Which way
the senate's going to go

34:14.936 --> 34:16.252
On the brandon bill
because the final vote

34:16.255 --> 34:18.455
Is being held up
by vice president susan ross.

34:18.457 --> 34:20.057
[ door opens ]

34:20.059 --> 34:21.458
Fitz: Susan.

34:21.460 --> 34:22.692
Mr. President.

34:22.694 --> 34:23.960
Your time's up.

34:23.961 --> 34:25.227
But, sir, i have
one more question.

34:25.230 --> 34:27.264
No more time.
No more questions.

34:27.266 --> 34:29.066
You have managed
to stall this bill

34:29.068 --> 34:30.634
And run everybody
out of this room,

34:30.636 --> 34:33.070
But you're not
gonna run me out.

34:33.072 --> 34:34.704
You are the<i> vice</i> president,
susan.

34:34.706 --> 34:35.839
I know that, sir.

34:35.841 --> 34:37.641
You don't know anything.

34:37.643 --> 34:40.060
You just got here.

34:40.061 --> 34:42.478
You are a fetus in the world
of washington politics.

34:42.481 --> 34:45.348
You can't possibly understand
what it takes

34:45.350 --> 34:47.484
To push a bill like this
through congress.

34:47.486 --> 34:49.052
The endless debate.

34:49.053 --> 34:50.619
The compromises.
The back-room dealings.

34:50.622 --> 34:52.622
And i will not allow you
to de-rail it.

34:52.624 --> 34:54.724
I will not allow you
to waste one more second.

34:54.726 --> 34:57.627
We need this bill now.

34:57.629 --> 35:00.630
To elevate the standard of
police conduct in this country,

35:00.632 --> 35:02.799
And to make sure that
what happened to brandon parker

35:02.801 --> 35:06.269
Never happens to anyone
ever again.

35:06.271 --> 35:08.205
Do you have a problem
with that, susan?

35:08.207 --> 35:10.507
No, sir, i don't, but --
good.

35:10.509 --> 35:13.543
Then get up to the hill and vote
the way you're supposed to.

35:13.545 --> 35:15.579
I understand, sir.

35:15.581 --> 35:17.814
Good.

35:17.816 --> 35:21.785
I understand what my role
is<i> supposed</i> to be.

35:21.787 --> 35:24.321
But i was clear with you
on the person you were getting

35:24.323 --> 35:25.722
When you asked me
to take this job.

35:25.724 --> 35:28.358
I am not here
to advance my own agenda.

35:28.360 --> 35:30.727
I am not here
staring into the oval office

35:30.729 --> 35:33.697
Imagining myself
with my feet up on your desk.

35:33.699 --> 35:36.700
And i am not here
to be your lap dog.

35:36.702 --> 35:40.303
The only reason i am here is
to help you make real change.

35:40.305 --> 35:42.706
But this bill,
it's not about real change.

35:42.708 --> 35:44.758
Have you read it?

35:44.759 --> 35:46.809
Because i understand
the importance of compromise,

35:46.812 --> 35:48.645
But that's all this bill is.

35:48.647 --> 35:50.747
Thousands
of tiny compromises

35:50.749 --> 35:53.583
That have rendered it
entirely useless.

35:53.585 --> 35:55.552
Unenforceable.

35:55.553 --> 35:57.520
I'm not the one
wasting your time here.

35:57.523 --> 36:00.357
This bill is wasting
your time.

36:00.359 --> 36:04.494
This bill is wasting
america's time.

36:06.832 --> 36:08.498
So, we keep
the reese amendment.

36:08.500 --> 36:10.901
Just sections
two and four.
What about six?

36:10.903 --> 36:13.737
Increasing the stop and search
threshold?
What's going on here?

36:13.739 --> 36:15.639
We'll never get it through.
They'll never read
this far.

36:15.641 --> 36:17.674
What is going on here?
Are we making progress?

36:17.676 --> 36:19.376
Are we ready to vote,
susan?

36:19.378 --> 36:21.578
We're pulling the bill, cy.
What?

36:21.580 --> 36:23.914
Susan was right.
It's 1,200 pages of nothing.

36:23.916 --> 36:25.582
We're making it better,
mr. Beene.

36:25.584 --> 36:26.883
We're gonna get it right
this time.

36:26.885 --> 36:28.952
You're gonna get killed
in the press,

36:28.954 --> 36:30.487
Is what you're gonna get.

36:30.489 --> 36:32.656
Not if we give them
something else to write about.

36:32.658 --> 36:34.224
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

36:34.226 --> 36:35.325
[ cheers and applause ]

36:35.327 --> 36:36.893
Thank you!
Thank you, mr. President!

36:36.895 --> 36:39.496
And thank you, people
of the great state of virginia!

36:39.498 --> 36:41.898
[ all cheer ]

36:41.900 --> 36:44.434
<i>It is with great humility</i>
<i>that i stand before you,</i>

36:44.436 --> 36:47.571
<i>Asking to represent you</i>
<i>in the senate today.</i>

36:47.573 --> 36:49.839
<i>From james monroe</i>
<i>to susan ross,</i>

36:49.841 --> 36:54.611
<i>Virginia has put forth some</i>
<i>of our nation's finest leaders.</i>

36:54.613 --> 36:56.646
<i>Half the battles</i>
<i>of the civil war were fought</i>

36:56.648 --> 36:58.949
<i>Right here</i>
<i>in this great state.</i>
How'd it go?

36:58.950 --> 37:01.251
Fine.
It's what you'd expect.

37:01.253 --> 37:03.420
You told them everything?
[ scoffs ]

37:03.422 --> 37:05.455
Yeah, the affair, the murder,
the hiding in the closet.

37:05.457 --> 37:06.723
All of it.

37:06.725 --> 37:08.558
Well,
the hard part is over.

37:08.560 --> 37:10.260
What you did
took courage.

37:10.262 --> 37:11.895
You should be proud
of that.

37:11.897 --> 37:13.763
I helped a lot of people
through my work.

37:13.765 --> 37:15.599
Would've helped even more
as mayor.

37:15.601 --> 37:17.634
I love my work.
I<i> am</i> my work.

37:17.636 --> 37:19.302
In 30 seconds,
all that gets overshadowed

37:19.304 --> 37:20.637
By a tabloid story.

37:20.639 --> 37:23.640
And i become
political poison forever.

37:23.642 --> 37:26.276
I am done.

37:26.278 --> 37:29.446
[ scoffs ]

37:29.448 --> 37:30.914
You did the right thing.

37:30.916 --> 37:32.816
Yeah, sure.
For natalie.

37:32.818 --> 37:34.951
For my conscience.
I guess i had to.

37:34.953 --> 37:36.720
And, hey,
no regrets, right?

37:36.722 --> 37:39.789
I mean, i get to tell people
i did the right thing.

37:39.791 --> 37:40.824
That's something.

37:40.825 --> 37:41.858
That's more
than something.

37:41.860 --> 37:42.959
That's everything.

37:42.961 --> 37:44.928
That's what saves you
in the end.

37:44.930 --> 37:47.497
You do the wrong thing,
then you're done.

37:47.499 --> 37:50.500
Not at first.

37:50.501 --> 37:53.502
It only feels like a misstep
at first, a compromise,

37:53.505 --> 37:55.905
A concession to reality,
a bad move well-played.

37:55.907 --> 37:58.808
But at some point, you're only
going in that direction.

37:58.810 --> 38:01.778
By the time you realize
how far down that path you are,

38:01.780 --> 38:02.846
You're lost.

38:02.848 --> 38:04.848
Everything is
unrecognizable.

38:04.850 --> 38:07.717
You are unrecognizable
to yourself.

38:07.719 --> 38:09.986
You find yourself doing things
you never thought you'd do

38:09.988 --> 38:11.755
In ways you never thought
you'd do them

38:11.757 --> 38:13.590
To save things
you're not even sure

38:13.592 --> 38:15.792
You want to save,
but you can't help it.

38:15.794 --> 38:17.394
That's when you're done.

38:17.396 --> 38:21.464
You are not done.

38:21.466 --> 38:23.933
You did
the right thing here.

38:23.935 --> 38:24.934
[ sighs ]

38:24.936 --> 38:27.404
I know it hurt.

38:27.406 --> 38:28.805
I know it hurt
to do it now.

38:28.807 --> 38:30.607
But...

38:30.609 --> 38:33.943
You know, "the time is
always right to do right."

38:34.813 --> 38:36.046
[ camera shutters clicking ]

38:36.048 --> 38:38.415
Man: Mr. Walker!
Mr. Walker!

38:38.417 --> 38:39.883
Woman: Mr. Walker!
Mr. Walker!

38:39.885 --> 38:42.952
Mr. Walker! Mr. Walker!

38:42.954 --> 38:44.321
[<i> camera shutters clicking</i> ]

38:44.323 --> 38:47.657
¶ the final curtain ¶

38:47.659 --> 38:52.462
¶ all of my friends,
let me make it real clear ¶

38:52.464 --> 38:54.831
So, have you decided
to take my case?

38:54.833 --> 38:57.934
Am i one
of your clients now?

38:57.936 --> 39:02.105
¶ ...Of which i'm trying
to be certain ¶

39:02.107 --> 39:03.973
You're right.

39:03.975 --> 39:05.742
You do know me.

39:05.744 --> 39:07.977
I looked
at all possible outcomes.

39:07.979 --> 39:09.779
I understand
what needs to be done.

39:09.781 --> 39:12.082
And i picked a side.

39:12.084 --> 39:13.350
But not yours.

39:13.352 --> 39:14.818
Hmm.

39:14.820 --> 39:16.386
